sentences: Denny Bruce (born in 1944 in Lancaster, Pennsylvania) is an American record producer and artist manager.
While living in Los Angeles in 1965 Denny was hired by Frank Zappa as a second drummer with The Mothers of Invention.
After the death of Magic Sam in 1969, Bruce worked as Tour Manager of Buffy Sainte-Marie.
In 1984 he managed "The Blasters" who released the album "Hard Line" on Slash/Warner Bros., as well as the Gun Club.
